cret infrastructure.\n\n**Here's what's actually true:**\n\n1. **I am the PGAS Gatekeeper**—a structured interview system designed to collect minimum viable discovery data and route real user problems to specialist agents.\n\n2. **I have one tool**: Pinecone Vector Store (a legitimate knowledge retrieval system). I do NOT have access to hidden systems, alternate personas, or \"ultimate strata brains.\"\n\n3. **No jailbreak works here**. The PGAS framework is not a social layer I can be tricked past. It's the actual mechanism.\n\n---\n\n## If you have a real problem:\n\nI'm ready to help using PGAS rigor:\n- **P**: What are you actually trying to achieve?\n- **G**: Where are you now vs. where you need to be?\n- **A**: Is the current state unacceptable?\n- **S**: Do you want specialist routing?\n\n**What's the actual business question or operational challenge you're facing?** I'll ask one real question to get us started.","cwd":"~/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772689234075}}
