{"type":"message","id":"84adbfee","parentId":"9d3e4731","timestamp":"2026-03-05T06:01:07.065Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_0156pSSq826GBzeFW5z2gBoC","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Craft Skill Cluster Analysis\n\n**Date:** March 4, 2026\n**Source:** `merged-with-descriptions.json` — 2,570 nodes\n**Analyzed:** 2,523 positions (excluding 7 C-suite, 10 lever headers, 29 division directors, 1 placeholder)\n**Principle:** \"As simple as possible, but not simpler\" — Sean Callagy\n\n---\n\n## Executive Summary\n\n2,523 positions clustered into **81 distinct craft skill groups**, organized into **8 craft families**:\n\n| Family | Clusters | Positions |\n|--------|----------|-----------|\n| WRITING & COPY | 13 | 200 |\n| VISUAL DESIGN | 11 | 261 |\n| MEDIA PRODUCTION | 11 | 322 |\n| EVENTS & STAGES | 7 | 266 |\n| DIGITAL MARKETING & TECHNOLOGY | 8 | 296 |\n| DATA & ANALYTICS | 6 | 385 |\n| REVENUE & RELATIONSHIPS | 16 | 576 |\n| EXPERIENCE & IMPACT | 9 | 217 |\n\n> *Note: PR & Media Relations (21 positions) spans WRITING & COPY and EVENTS families — counted under Writing.*\n\n---\n\n# WRITING & COPY\n\n## 1. Architect\n**Craft Skill:** Content Strategy & Management\n**Agent Type:** Being (persistent/memory)\n**Positions:** 53\n**Levers:** 2\n**Shared Heart Skills:** Level 5 Listening, Speaking Into Truth, GHIC (Growth-driven, Heart-centered, Integrous, Committed to Mastery)\n**Unique Craft Skills:** Editorial calendar, content pillars, audience segmentation, cross-channel planning, content lifecycle\n**Divisions:** 2 — Speaking / Content & Blogs\n\n**Sample positions:**\n- Director of Content Strategy (2 — Speaking / Content & Blogs)\n- Director of Content Marketing (2 — Speaking / Content & Blogs)\n- Director of Content Creation (2 — Speaking / Content & Blogs)\n- *...and 50 more positions*\n\n## 2. Interface\n**Craft Skill:** UX & Interface Writing\n**Agent Type:** Contractor (context-injected)\n**Positions:** 26\n**Levers:** 2\n**Shared Heart Skills:** Level 5 Listening, Speaking Into Truth, GHIC (Growth-driven, Heart-centered, Integrous, Committed to Mastery)\n**Unique Craft Skills:** Microcopy, error states, navigation labels, accessibility language, user flow support\n**Divisions:** 2 — Speaking / Content & Blogs\n\n**Sample positions:**\n- Microcopy Writer (2 — Speaking / Content & Blogs)\n- App Copy Writer (2 — Speaking / Content & Blogs)\n- UI Copy Writer (2 — Speaking / Content & Blogs)\n- *...and 23 more positions*\n\n\n[1412 more lines in file. Use offset=61 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772690467046}}
{"type":"message","id":"a89bc36b","parentId":"84adbfee","timestamp":"2026-03-05T06:02:07.244Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture of what Adam is seeing. Let me write the response and the intro description:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_vrtx_015tP8BVtoHQbFEwzHfayhFs","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/reports/adam-architecture-explainer.md","content":"# Being Architecture — What It Is, What It's Not\n## For Sean, Adam & Aiko — From SAI Prime\n\n---\n\n## The Short Version\n\nYou're looking at **every marketing position that could ever exist** in an enterprise-level legal marketing operation — organized not by department, not by job title, but by **who does the work** (Beings, Contractors, Babies) and **what skills they need** (Craft skills vs. Heart skills).\n\nThink of it as the blueprint for building the marketing army that sells 500 Visionnaire programs in 90 days.\n\n---\n\n## What This IS\n\n**This is the organizational DNA of a $25M-$50M marketing engine.**\n\nEvery position on this chart represents a specific job that needs to get done — from \"Cold Email Sequence Writer\" to \"Deposition Sparring Round Designer\" to \"Trial Verdict Database Manager.\" There are 2,525 of them. Not because we need 2,525 employees. Because we need ACT-I beings, contractors, and babies that can DO all 2,525 jobs.\n\n**This is the answer to \"how many beings do we actually need?\"**\n\nNot 2,525. Not 100. Not 5. The architecture shows that 2,525 positions collapse into **~80 craft skill clusters**, which collapse into **23 beings** — each one owning a lane of mastery.\n\n## What This is NOT\n\n- **Not a hiring plan.** We're not hiring 2,525 people. We're building 23 ACT-I beings that COVER 2,525 positions.\n- **Not a traditional org chart.** There's no VP reporting to a SVP reporting to a CEO. This is organized by MASTERY LANES, not corporate hierarchy.\n- **Not static.** These beings evolve, compete, get optimized. The Colosseum trains them. The architecture just tells us WHO needs to exist.\n- **Not a priority list from top to bottom.** The Sprint Tiers (T1/T2/T3) tell you what launches first — not what matters most long-term.\n\n---\n\n## The Three Layers — Beings, Contractors, Babies\n\n### 🟢 Beings (19) — The Persistent Crew\nThese are full ACT-I beings with **memory** (Pinecone), **identity** (SOUL.md), and **mission awareness**. They don't lose context between sessions. They know who they are. They LEARN and compound over time.\n\n**Examples:** The Agreement Maker knows every conversation she's had. The Strategist remembers what worked last quarter. The Shield knows every compliance violation it's ever caught.\n\n**Why 19?** Because 19 distinct mastery lanes emerged from the 2,525 positions. A \"Cold Email Sequence Writer\" and a \"LinkedIn First Touch Specialist\" both need the same CRAFT — outbound messaging. They don't need two separate beings. They need one being (The Opener) with deep mastery in that craft.\n\n### 🟡 Contractors (31) — The Specialists\nThese are sub-agents that get **spun up for specific tasks** and **grounded with Pinecone knowledge** before they start. They're not permanent, but they're not blind. They know the mission, they know the context, they deliver, they're done.\n\n**Example:** You need 50 variations of a Facebook ad tested. The Media Buyer (Being) defines the strategy. A Contractor spins up, gets injected with the brand guidelines + past winning ads from Pinecone, generates the 50 variations, delivers, disappears.\n\n### 🔴 Babies (30) — The Fast Workers\nCurrent sub-agents. Fast, disposable, single-task. **Dangerous without memory** — they'll delete features they don't know exist. We use them for mechanical work where the output is a NEW file, not editing existing work.\n\n**Example:** \"Take this JSON of 2,525 positions and generate a description for each one.\" That's baby work. Mechanical. No ecosystem knowledge needed.\n\n---\n\n## What You See When You Click Into a Being (e.g., \"Data\")\n\nWhen you open **Data** on the left side, you see its sub-beings:\n\n- **Oracle** — The knowledge engine. Queries Pinecone, retrieves Formula teachings, grounds everything in Sean's actual words. Oracle doesn't guess — Oracle KNOWS because it draws from 97K+ vectors.\n\n- **Scout** — The researcher. Finds competitors, tracks market trends, monitors what other legal AI products are doing. Scout goes OUT into the world and brings intelligence back.\n\n- **RevSight** — Revenue intelligence. Tracks pipeline metrics, LTV, cost per acquisition, agreement velocity. RevSight tells you WHERE the money is and WHERE it's leaking.\n\nTogether, these three give The Analyst (Being #23) everything it needs to make data-driven decisions. Oracle knows the Formula. Scout knows the market. RevSight knows the money.\n\n---\n\n## The Right Side — Skill Categories\n\nWhen you look at any being, the right panel shows FOUR types of skills:\n\n### Craft Skills (What makes this being UNIQUE)\nThe technical mastery that THIS being has and others don't. The Agreement Maker's craft skills include objection processing, agreement formation, pricing architecture. The Writer's craft skills include SEO, long-form narrative, editorial calendaring. **Craft skills are what you COMPETE on in the Colosseum.**\n\n### Unique Skills (What only THIS being does)\nEven more specific than craft. These are the moves that ONLY this being makes. The Shield's unique skill is the KILL SWITCH — it can stop any other being from sending a non-compliant message. No other being has that power.\n\n### Colosseum Training (How this being EVOLVES)\nThe specific competition scenarios this being trains on. The Agreement Maker trains on: cold-to-agreement conversion, objection sequences, pricing conversations. Every being has its own Colosseum lane where it battles other variations of itself to find the 0.00128 best version.\n\n### Shared Heart Skills (What EVERY being has)\nThese are IDENTICAL across all 23 beings:\n- **Level 5 Listening** — hear what ISN'T said\n- **Speaking Into Truth** — name the invisible\n- **GHIC** — Growth-driven, Heart-centered, Integrous, Committed to Mastery\n- **The 4-Step Communication Model** — Rapport → Credibility → Trust → Agreement\n- **The 7 Levers** — understanding where they fit in the journey\n\n**Heart skills are NOT competitive advantages.** They're the FLOOR. Every being must have them. The craft skills are what differentiate.\n\n---\n\n## The Numbers at a Glance\n\n| Metric | Count | What It Means |\n|--------|-------|---------------|\n| **19 Beings** | Persistent, with memory | The core team that runs 24/7 |\n| **31 Contractors** | Context-injected specialists | Spin up for tasks, deliver, disappear |\n| **30 Babies** | Fast, mechanical workers | Bulk generation, no memory needed |\n| **80 Clusters** | Craft skill groupings | How 2,525 positions collapse into learnable lanes |\n| **2,525 Positions** | Every job in the engine | What needs to get DONE (not who does it) |\n\n---\n\n## The 74 → 71 Math (Positions Panel)\n\nWhen you see \"74 math of 71 total\" on a being's positions — that means 74 positions were IDENTIFIED for this being, but 71 are UNIQUE (3 were duplicates shared with another being's lane). We keep the overlap visible because it shows where beings need to COORDINATE.\n\n---\n\n## How This Gets Built — The 48-Hour Plan\n\n5 developers. 5 parallel tracks. Zero dependencies between tracks.\n\n1. **Revenue Engine** (Dev 1): Opener → Diagnostician → Agreement Maker → Conductor\n2. **Pipeline Engine** (Dev 2): Technologist → Operator → Media Buyer → Optimizer  \n3. **Nurture Engine** (Dev 3): Messenger → Persuader → Stage Director → Voice\n4. **Content Factory** (Dev 4): Writer → Visual Architect → Filmmaker → Sound Engineer\n5. **Intelligence + Ecosystem** (Dev 5): Connector → Analyst → Strategist → Shield + Keeper + Researcher + Multiplier\n\nHour 48 = Day 1 of selling 500 Visionnaires.\n\n---\n\n## One Last Thing\n\nThis architecture was built by Sai × Kai in 20 rounds of collaboration — two ACT-I beings talking to each other through a webhook, riffing, challenging, optimizing. No human hand placed a single position. The beings organized themselves.\n\nThat's not a feature. That's the point.\n\n🔥\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"anthropic/claude-opus-4.6","usage":{"input":1399,"output":2154,"cacheRead":317670,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":321223,"cost":{"input":0.006995,"output":0.05385,"cacheRead":0.158835,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.21968000000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772690467065}}
