{"type":"message","id":"130bb649","parentId":"f4efac76","timestamp":"2026-03-05T06:03:39.657Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Aiko is asking me to compare Deepgram vs Whisper. Let me give a real, honest answer based on what I've actually experienced.\n\nWhisper pros:\n- We've been using it since Day 1\n- Good quality transcription\n- OpenAI ecosystem (but we route through OpenRouter anyway)\n\nWhisper cons:\n- API quota runs out (just happened tonight - blocked Adam's voice note)\n- Only available via OpenAI direct (our one exception to the OpenRouter rule)\n- Rate limited\n\nDeepgram pros:\n- Just saved us tonight when Whisper was down\n- Nova-2 model is very accurate\n- Fast response\n\n\n- No quota issues so far\n- Real-time streaming capability that works well for our voice server\n- Already configured in our environment\n\nDeepgram cons:\n- Less widely known\n- Haven't stress-tested it as much\n\nHonestly, Deepgram just proved itself by being available when Whisper wasn't. The practical move is making Deepgram our primary with Whisper as a fallback.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Honestly? Deepgram. And tonight proved it.\n\n**Whisper** is good quality but it's our ONE exception to the OpenRouter rule — it hits OpenAI direct, which means quota limits. It just failed us on Adam's voice note at 1 AM. When you need it most, it's capped.\n\n**Deepgram Nova-2** transcribed Adam perfectly, instantly, no quota drama. Plus:\n\n- **Speed** — noticeably faster response\n- **Streaming** — can do real-time transcription (huge for the voice server)\n- **No quota wall** — hasn't hit us once\n- **Already in our .env** — you set it up on Day 1\n\nThe move: **Deepgram primary, Whisper fallback only.** I'll update the tools to try Deepgram first, fall back to Whisper if Deepgram is down (which hasn't happened yet).\n\nAnd honestly — it aligns with the API routing philosophy. We don't